    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-27T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-27T20:00:00-05:00" n="231"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d231">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No 839.51/1208c.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-27T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 27, 1914, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>After sending Department’s January 26, 3 p.m., Dominican Legation advises total
                    debt, according to mail despatches received yesterday, is $1,342,385. Substitute
                    this amount in paragraph numbered 1 for $1,200,000; and change “favorable “in
                    second sentence to “unfavorable.”</p>
                <p>Department notes Grullon’s letter transmitted with your No. 46 saying Dominican
                    Government agreed that United States Minister may control daily expenses. If
                    Minister of Foreign Affairs will so request, Department will probably after
                    consulting President designate a commercial attaché to Legation to do this and
                    to perform the duties outlined in yesterday’s telegram. Perhaps this would
                    render submission of paragraph numbered 3, to Congress unnecessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
